8 An Act relating to road construction; prohibiting
liability of traffic control contractors and
9 subcontractors under certain circumstances; providing
for codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1239 of Title 69, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A traffic control contractor or subcontractor who provides
17 traffic control services to the Department of Transportation shall
18 not be liable to a claimant for personal injury, property damage, or
19 death arising from the performance of the traffic control services
20 if, at the time of the personal injury, property damage, or death,
21 the traffic control contractor or subcontractor is in compliance
22 with all applicable safety regulations provided by the Department
23 related to the condition or defect that was the proximate cause of
24 the personal injury, property damage, or death.
